<paragraph blockId="7.[167,779,533,1104]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis box="[168,777,639,663]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,639,663]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alves-Silva, R. M. Silveira &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[341,573,639,663]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="murrillii">
<emphasis box="[341,573,639,663]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fomitiporia murrillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified by
</emphasis>
the following characters: basidiome perennial, ungulate (
<figureCitation box="[227,315,706,730]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); hymenophoral surface with circular to angular pores, 4–6 per mm (
<figureCitation box="[488,572,739,764]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); context homogeneous, woody, cinnamon-brown (
<figureCitation box="[540,626,773,797]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[168,231,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-35@5.[168,1419,160,1956]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia langloisii. B. F. maxonii. C. F. murrillii. D. F. neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); hyphal system dimitic, with generative hyphae hyaline, yellowish, thin-walled, septate (
<figureCitation box="[395,479,840,864]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
); skeletal hyphae yellowish, thick-walled, nonseptate (
<figureCitation box="[445,531,874,898]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
); basidiospores dextrinoid, subglobose to globose, hyaline, thick-walled, 5.5–7 × 4.5–6 μm (
<figureCitation box="[308,391,941,965]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Dai YC &amp; Cui BC &amp; Decock C" box="[413,576,941,965]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" pagination="375 - 380" refId="ref5189" refString="Dai YC, Cui BC, Decock C (2008) A new species of Fomitiporia Hymenochaetaceae, Basidiomycota) from China based on morphological and molecular characters. Mycological Research 112 (1): 375 - 380. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. mycres. 2007.11.020" type="journal article" year="2008">Dai et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
